description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join Homerton University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust as Head of the Integrated Independence Team. This is a senior post within the IMRS divisional management team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Homerton is an innovative Foundation Trust providing a wide range of services to its local community and specialist services on a regional level. Located in the East End of London it is close to the heart of the capital and our local population is young and culturally diverse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Homerton Hospital overall as recently rated ‘Outstanding’ following a CQC inspection in January 2020. Urgent Care and Medical Services have also been rated as Outstanding.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will lead a team of over 50 staff made up of doctors, therapists and nurses as well as care assistants, social workers and associated clerical staff. The successful candidate will have experience of leading a diverse workforce and be able to work both strategically and operationally within complex systems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The postholder will lead a fully integrated team providing a full range of intermediate care and reablement services across health and social care systems in Hackney. The team plays a pivotal role in helping vulnerable patients to be cared for at home rather than in hospital as well as supporting patients to be discharged from hospital as early as possible.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The postholder will work within the management structure at Homerton but will also work closely with partner colleagues at the London Borough of Hackney.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Depending on experience, an exceptional candidate may also be given a wider remit covering Adult Community Nursing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: 30th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Osian Powell, Divisional Operations Director for Integrated Medicine &amp; Rehabilitation Services on email: osian.powell1@nhs.net or phone: 0208-510-7206 or Rahima Khatun, Divisional PA, on email: Rahima.Khatun9@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
